# ====================================================================================================================================
# TC_01_STAFF.feature
# ====================================================================================================================================
@maps @regression @staff
Feature: TC_01_STAFF - Map Printing by Herd Number

  # Migrated from legacy "Regression Suite for Map Printing with Herd" (AT-TC-01, 02, 04).
  # Legacy AT-TC-03 was commented out as a depleted case and is not carried forward.
  #
  # BUSINESS FLOW
  #   An internal map printing user searches a herd on the Map Printing screen, chooses the
  #   parcels and map layout to render, and requests generation. The screen must also refuse
  #   a search with no herd number.
  #
  # WHAT THIS VALIDATES
  #   1. A map can be generated for a single selected parcel of a herd.
  #   2. Searching with an empty herd field raises the mandatory-field error.
  #   3. A map can be generated across all parcels of a herd.

  @staffdata @herds:4:submitted
  Background:
    Given the staff user is logged in to the BISS internal portal as "agr11612"
    And the staff user is on the Map Printing screen

  @e2e @map-generation
  Scenario: Staff generates herd maps for single and all parcel selections

    # SECTION 1 - AT-TC-01 (BISSAGL-14969)
    # Validates: a map is accepted for generation when one parcel of a submitted herd is
    # selected against a Full Colour Ortho A4 layout with the legend enabled.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next submitted herd for scheme year "2023"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single              |
      | mapType | Full Color Ortho A4 |
      | legend  | yes                 |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted

    # SECTION 2 - AT-TC-02 (BISSAGL-14968)
    # Validates: the herd number is mandatory - searching with an empty field is rejected.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing with no herd number
    Then the staff user should see the validation error "Herd number required."

    # SECTION 3 - AT-TC-04 (BISSAGL-14966)
    # Validates: generation is accepted when every parcel on the herd is selected, proving
    # the multi-parcel path as well as the single-parcel path in Section 1.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next submitted herd for scheme year "2023"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | all                 |
      | mapType | Full Color Ortho A4 |
      | legend  | yes                 |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted


# ====================================================================================================================================
# TC_02_STAFF.feature
# ====================================================================================================================================
@maps @regression @staff
Feature: TC_02_STAFF - Map Printing by Parcel Number

  # Migrated from legacy "Regression Suite for Map Printing with Parcel"
  # (AT-TC-01, 02, 04, 05, 07-14). Legacy AT-TC-03 and AT-TC-06 were commented out as
  # depleted cases and are not carried forward.
  #
  # BUSINESS FLOW
  #   An internal map printing user searches by LPIS parcel rather than herd, selects a map
  #   layout - either a preset (Ortho / Inspection Discovery) or a custom composition of
  #   imagery, raster and vector layers - and requests generation. Every field required by
  #   the chosen layout must be enforced before generation is allowed.
  #
  # WHAT THIS VALIDATES
  #   1. Preset and custom layouts both generate, at A3 and A4, for single and all parcels.
  #   2. Each mandatory selection raises its own error when omitted: parcel number, parcel
  #      selection, map type, imagery layer, vector layer.
  #   3. The Map Printing tab is not visible to a non-internal user.

  @staffdata @parcels:14
  Background:
    Given the staff user is logged in to the BISS internal portal as "agr11612"
    And the staff user is on the Map Printing screen
    And the staff user is searching by parcel

  @e2e @map-generation @validation
  Scenario: Staff generates parcel maps across layouts and is blocked on every missing field

    # SECTION 1 - AT-TC-01 (BISSAGL-14997)
    # Validates: the Inspection Discovery preset generates for a single parcel.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single               |
      | mapType | Inspection Discovery |
      | legend  | yes                  |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted

    # SECTION 2 - AT-TC-02 (BISSAGL-14996)
    # Validates: a custom layout generates when imagery, raster and vector are all supplied.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single               |
      | mapType | Custom Layer A4      |
      | imagery | 2009 Low Flown Ortho |
      | raster  | Raster 1:5000        |
      | vector  | default              |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted

    # SECTION 3 - AT-TC-04 (BISSAGL-14993)
    # Validates: the Full Colour Ortho A4 preset generates for a single parcel.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single              |
      | mapType | Full Color Ortho A4 |
      | legend  | yes                 |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted

    # SECTION 4 - AT-TC-05 (BISSAGL-14988)
    # Validates: the parcel number is mandatory when searching by parcel.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing with no parcel number
    Then the staff user should see the validation error "Parcel number required."

    # SECTION 5 - AT-TC-07 (BISSAGL-14986)
    # Validates: A3 generates across all parcels returned by a parcel search - the multi
    # parcel path at a different page size from Section 3.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | all                 |
      | mapType | Full Color Ortho A3 |
      | legend  | yes                 |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted

    # SECTION 6 - AT-TC-08 (BISSAGL-14983)
    # Validates: a custom layout generates across all parcels, combining the custom-layer
    # path of Section 2 with the all-parcels path of Section 5.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | all                  |
      | mapType | Custom Layer A4      |
      | imagery | 2008 Low Flown Ortho |
      | raster  | Raster 1:5000        |
      | vector  | default              |
    Then the map generation request should be accepted

    # SECTION 7 - AT-TC-09 (BISSAGL-14982)
    # Legacy carries the note "Fix case by next week" and has NO assertion - it searches a
    # future scheme year and stops. The intended check ("no results warning") is commented
    # out in legacy. Reproduced as a search only; the warning assertion needs writing.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2025"

    # SECTION 8 - AT-TC-10 (BISSAGL-14981)
    # Validates: opening and dismissing the parcel selector without choosing a parcel
    # raises the selection error.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user opens and dismisses the "parcelSelect" selector without choosing a value
    Then the staff user should see the validation error "select a parcel required"

    # SECTION 9 - AT-TC-11 (BISSAGL-14980)
    # Validates: with a parcel chosen, dismissing the map type selector raises its error.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single |
    And the staff user opens and dismisses the "mapTypeSelect" selector without choosing a value
    Then the staff user should see the validation error "select a map type required"

    # SECTION 10 - AT-TC-12 (BISSAGL-14979)
    # Validates: a custom layout requires an imagery layer - dismissing it raises its error.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single          |
      | mapType | Custom Layer A4 |
    And the staff user opens and dismisses the "imagerySelect" selector without choosing a value
    Then the staff user should see the validation error "select an imagery layer required"

    # SECTION 11 - AT-TC-13 (BISSAGL-14978)
    # Validates: a custom layout requires a vector layer even once imagery is chosen.
    When the staff user searches Map Printing for the next LPIS parcel for scheme year "2024"
    And the staff user requests a map with the following settings
      | parcels | single               |
      | mapType | Custom Layer A4      |
      | imagery | 2009 Low Flown Ortho |
    And the staff user opens and dismisses the "vectorSelect" selector without choosing a value
    Then the staff user should see the validation error "select a vector layer required"

    # SECTION 12 - AT-TC-14 (BISSAGL-14977)
    # Validates: Map Printing is restricted by role - a non-internal user cannot see the tab.
    When the staff user re-logs in to the BISS internal portal as "agr5033"
    Then the staff user should not have access to the "Map Printing" tab


